title: chapter3_OmenCity_Tailors_George1
tags:
---
George: What are you doing here?
Player: I'm just taking a look. 
Player: Is that not allowed, my Lord?
George: Isn't this all a little fine and expensive for someone like you? 
George: Or are you trying to move up in the world by dressing in something more impressive than that burlap sack you always wear? 
George: Ha! I bet you have no taste anyway.
Player: I do have taste!
George: Oh? 
George: Prove it, then. 
George: Come here and look at these ribbons.
    -> Player: Fine! But not because you asked me to.
        George: Ugh! 
        George: Stop grumbling and just do as you're told for once.
    -> Erm, okay.
        George: No backchat? 
        George: Maybe you are finally learning some etiquette.
George: Now, little mouse. 
George: What colour ribbon would you buy? 
George: Not that you have the money, of course. 
George: This is all completely theoretical.
    -> Player: Red.
      <<set $colour = "Red">>
        George: A classic choice.
        George: Similar to the one I'm wearing but made from a softer fabric.
    -> Player: Blue.
      <<set $colour = "Blue">>
        George: A popular choice.
        George: Personally, I don't wear a lot of blue but I hear it is quite popular amongst the nobles in the Capital, thanks to Princess Alice.
    -> Player: Green.
      <<set $colour = "Green">>
        George: An interesting choice.
        George: My sister has been known to wear green on occasion. 
        George: People say it goes well with the colour of our eyes.
    -> Player: Yellow.
      <<set $colour = "Yellow">>
        George: A bold choice.
        George: Many nobles such as myself choose to wear gold and similar shades to signify our status.
Player: It's not all about you!
George: Hmm...
George: Yes I can say from that assessment of your abilities that you do indeed have no taste in fashion at all.
Player: What? 
<<if $colour == "Red">>
    <<set $descriptor = "classic">>
<<elseif $colour == "Blue">>
    <<set $descriptor = "popular">>
<<elseif $colour == "Green">>
    <<set $descriptor = "interesting">>
<<elseif $colour == "Yellow">>
    <<set $descriptor = "bold">>
<<endif>>
Player: But you said it was a {$descriptor} choice!
George: No taste at all…
Player: Well, I don't care what you think. 
Player: I like that colour.
George: Ha! 
George: See you around, little mouse. 
George: I think we're overdue for a rematch.
===

